Legal trouble, payola scandal ===

Freed's career was significantly affected when it was shown that he had accepted payola (payments from record companies to play specific records), a practice that was highly controversial at the time.
He initially denied taking payola but later admitted to his fans that he had accepted bribes.
In 1960, payola was made illegal.
